narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Develop entrepreneurship ideas into a venture and continue modifying ideas into perfection
Important frameworks for conceiving, organizing, and launching a startup social venture.

narratives.question_text: How well did the knowledge, skills, and insights gained in this class align with your expectations?
comments: Largely aligned, though sometimes the coursework overwhelmed my time and ability to think creatively about the venture.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of the course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strenghs: Very interactive, the book is really good Weaknesses: The professor never dedicated one single moment to speak to my team in person during class exercises

Strengths: Clear-outlined training on developing a social-focused venture. Throughout the semester, many social entrepreneurs have been invited to the class to share their experiences. This has been super helpful to give students a better sense of entrepreneurship. Weaknesses: It is challenging to change ideas in the middle of the semester. Homework or assignments sometimes feel overwhelming and do not necessarily help with the idea generation and development.

Strengths: excellent frameworks for designing and launching a startup. Weaknesses: not enough feedback from and direct engagement with instructor on the venture early enough to make important and necessary adjustments to fully maximize the venture.

narratives.question_text: What advice would you give to a student considering taking this class?
comments: Take it only if you are really wanting to start a venture of your own
I suggest having a relatively clear vision of a venture you want to develop or joining a group with a defined vision for a venture. Don't lose faith among those weekly assignments.
Make sure to engage directly with the professor early on to get feedback, given the fast pace of the course.
